{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-05","name":"Maccus","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Maccus","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Maccus"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Maccus Filius Undweyn Norseman","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1090–1150","fullLifespan":"1090–1150","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/jyygi/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7702-113920-907-12/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/140402032","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7702-113920-907-12/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7702-113920-907-12/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7770-119374-2552-10/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/158877486","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7770-119374-2552-10/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7770-119374-2552-10/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7776-119134-2016-97/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/158293137","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7776-119134-2016-97/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7776-119134-2016-97/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7701-113920-959-12/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/140402179","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7701-113920-959-12/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7701-113920-959-12/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7768-130080-8066-7/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/186441491","headline":"From the Memoirs of Maxwell of Pollok.","description":"II.--Maccus, who gave name to the Barony and Family of Maxwell. Died c. 1150.","@type":"MediaObject"}],"popularStory":{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7768-130080-8066-7/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/186441491","headline":"From the Memoirs of Maxwell of Pollok.","description":"II.--Maccus, who gave name to the Barony and Family of Maxwell. Died c. 1150.","@type":"MediaObject"},"birthDate":"+1090","birthPlace":{"address":"Springwood House, Roxburghshire, Scotland","geo":{"latitude":55.58333,"longitude":-2.45,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1150","deathPlace":{"address":"France","geo":{"latitude":46.0,"longitude":2.0,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"burialDate":"+1150","burialPlace":{"address":"Rouen, Normandie, France","geo":{"latitude":49.4447,"longitude":1.0933,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nMaccus was the son of Udewyn. The surname Maxwell is apparently derived from his name, as Maxwell springs from Maccuswell in Springwood Roxburgh.\n\nIn William the Lion's reign Liulph styled son of Maccus, had a son Uchtred and a daughter Cecilla ( with lands in Maccustoun (Maxton) wife of Robert de Berkley and Edmund de Macheswel (perhaps another son of Maccus.) William the Lion confirmed c1200 to Robert (styled son of Maccus lands in Lesedwin, Roxburghshire which Herbert de Maccuswell his sheriff had by his precept delivered to him.\n\nThe history of the builders of Caerlaverock Castle can be traced to Undwin and his son Maccus in the eleventh century; Maccus gave his name to the barony of Maccuswell, or Maxwell. His grandson, John de Maccuswell (d.1241), was first Lord Maxwell of Caerlaverock. The Baronies of Maxwell and Caerlaverock then passed down through the male line, sometimes collaterally. Robert de Maxwell of Maxwell, Caerlaverock and Mearns (d.1409) rebuilt Caerlaverock castle and was succeeded by Herbert Maxwell of Caerlaverock (d.1420)\n\nHe was a witness in 1116 of David, Earl of Cumberland, who would become King David I. into the possessions of the Church of Glasgow.","sourceList":[{"title":"  Memoirs of the Maxwells of Pollok   Volume 1 - Memoirs & charters - Pedigree of Main Line of Maxwell Family, Page xlv","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://digital.nls.uk/histories-of-scottish-families/archive/96744288#?c=0&m=0&s=0&cv=58&xywh=-1290%2C-189%2C5079%2C3765","sourceUri":"QV2W-LY8"},{"title":"Ancestry Family Trees","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceUri":"3TXZ-FXR"},{"title":"MACCUS to MAXTONE, Migration of a name, 1100-1700","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://electricscotland.com/webclans/m/maxtone.html","sourceUri":"S1TP-TSK"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"2","year":"1090","date":"1090","place":"Springwood House, Roxburghshire, Scotland"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1090","date":"1090","place":"Perthshire, Scotland","age":"0","id":"G4JR-71X"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1090","da